%% Service chain for Cargo Shipping (DDD example).
%% This is the "皇冠上的寶石" artefact — every external integration and inter-service
%% call shows up here.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Cust as Customer
    participant FE as Booking UI
    participant BS as Booking Service
    participant RS as Routing Service
    participant HS as Handling Service
    participant TS as Tracking Service
    participant Bus as Event Bus
    participant Email as Email Provider

    Cust->>FE: Submit booking (origin, destination, deadline)
    FE->>BS: POST /cargos
    BS->>BS: Generate TrackingId
    BS->>FE: 201 + TrackingId
    BS->>Bus: CargoBookedEvent
    Bus->>TS: CargoBookedEvent
    TS->>TS: Create empty tracking view

    Cust->>FE: Request route options
    FE->>BS: GET /cargos/{id}/routes
    BS->>RS: fetchRoutesForSpecification(spec)
    RS->>BS: List<Itinerary>
    BS->>FE: 200 + itinerary candidates

    Cust->>FE: Choose itinerary
    FE->>BS: PUT /cargos/{id}/itinerary
    BS->>BS: Persist + transition to ROUTED
    BS->>Bus: CargoAssignedToRouteEvent
    Bus->>TS: CargoAssignedToRouteEvent
    Bus->>Email: send_booking_confirmation()

    Note over HS: Operations register events as cargo travels

    HS->>HS: registerHandlingEvent(LOAD at SHANGHAI)
    HS->>Bus: HandlingEventRegistered
    Bus->>TS: HandlingEventRegistered
    TS->>TS: Update view, recompute misdirection
    Bus->>BS: HandlingEventRegistered (for invariants)

    Cust->>FE: Track cargo
    FE->>TS: GET /tracking/{id}
    TS->>FE: CargoTrackingView
    FE->>Cust: Render tracking page
